2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses the Signal-to-Interference-and-Noise-Ratio (SINR) model, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with connectivity in wireless networks, which is a topic of interest in social and information networks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses phase transitions and critical values, which are concepts commonly studied in data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with wireless networks, which can be considered as a type of multiagent system.
